If you adore the American Songbook—the greatest musical expression of American hopes and dreams—then Lyrics & Lyricists will take you straight to heaven.

Where else do today’s shining stars of Broadway, jazz and cabaret sing the soaring classic standards—and tell you the incredible stories behind them? Nowhere but here, in intimate shows that sweep you up in this spellbinding music.

Lyrics & Lyricists receives underwriting support from Gilda and Henry Block; The Edythe Kenner Foundation; and the Hite Foundation, Inc.
ChildNode.Name: Lyrics and Lyricists

ChildNode.FeatureItemsContent:
At the intersection of sound and sight, Seeing Music presents visionary interpretations of beloved masterworks by virtuosi from the worlds of music and art.

The visual media of painting, film, video and set design—including the debut of two installations commissioned by 92Y—inform and illuminate music by Bach, Beethoven, Mussorgsky and more in performances by brilliant musicians.

The Seeing Music festival is underwritten by Eva and John Usdan, Martin and Suzi Oppenheimer and the Adele and John Gray Endowment Fund.
ChildNode.Name: Seeing Music

ChildNode.FeatureItemsContent:
Soundspace is a new way to hear music. Soundspace cracks open the formality of traditional classical concerts to bring openness and light to performance.

The shows take place in 92Y’s atmospheric Buttenwieser Hall—in a space where artists, composers and audience can share the moment, the music, and even the stage in pursuit of discovering what live performance can be. In our first season, artists bring their passion projects to Soundspace. One concert traces a single theme for 300 years, others link Beethoven with composers of today, while still others give voice to cultural heritages nearly lost. Join us, and be part of the experience.
ChildNode.Name: Soundspace

The inner lives of great people are often more mysterious and fascinating than their public lives. Dr. Gail Saltz invites experts and brings her own expertise to bear as she examines the psychology of people who have shaped history.


Dr. Gail Saltz is Clinical Associate Professor of Psychiatry at The New York Presbyterian Hospital, psychoanalyst with The New York Psychoanalytic Institute, columnist, bestselling author and television commentator including frequent contributing to the "Today Show," CNN and MSNBC. She is the emotional wellness contributor to Health Magazine and Health.com, Chair the of 92Y 7 Days of Genius Advisory Committee and Consultant and Event Moderator for the Clinton Foundation’s Health Matters Initiative.

ChildNode.FeatureItemsContent:
Ralph Buultjens, a leading analyst of world affairs, examines critical issues in international politics. Buultjens is a professor at New York University and the former Nehru Professor/Professorial Fellow at the University of Cambridge. He was awarded the Toynbee Prize for Social Sciences and is the author of 10 books on world affairs.

Due to the fast-changing nature of global politics, topics may change.

The World Politics with Ralph Buultjens Series is underwritten in memory of Harold W. and Ida L. Goldstein by the Estate of Sanford Goldstein.
